<td>
    <p>What is it?
    <p>LVSM is the linux virtual server manager.  It is a package which is designed to simplify creation and management of <a href=http://www.linuxvirtualserver.org>LVS</a> based clusters.
    <p>LVSM development <i>was</i> sponsored by <a href=http://www.penguincomputing.com>Penguin Computing</a>, until they decided to abandon the project and terminate my employment (5/24).

    <p>Given that, lvsm will move forward, but now in my spare time with my rag-tag collection of old boxes instead of full time with a half rack of machines.

    <p>What does LVSM have to offer?  
    <ul>
    <li>Level 4 load balancing
    <li>High Availability
    <li>Service level monitoring
    <li>Remote web based admistration
    <li>On the fly configuration 
    <li>Cluster Statistics 
    </ul>
</td></tr></table>

